Date: 7/10/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: <i>Crook<i>: Same as <i>cronk</i>, [`ill, not at all well'] but less so, perhaps. Often <i>a bit crook.</i> Both these words are slang. Here, they are applied to men, dogs and horses. (C.)
Notes: (Acland Gloss.)

